This paper is primarily focused on speech recognition, which falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP). Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses optimization techniques such as neural connection pruning and parameter quantization, which are related to machine learning and optimization, respectively. Therefore, cs.SD (Sound) and cs.LG (Learning) are also likely sub-categories. The paper also mentions the use of neural network topologies and optimization techniques, which are common in computer vision (CV) and control systems (SY). Therefore, cs.CV and cs.SY are also possible sub-categories.
